WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Pendentive' is a Workbench game based on the proverbial
'align-3-tiles-of-the-same-type' style of play, but with a
different twist: all tiles are placed as if they were suspended
from the top. As you align 3 or more tiles of the same type
together, either vertically or horizontally, these tiles are
then removed. If there are tiles right under the removed tiles,
those tiles will "fall" towards the bottom of the game board.

  Sounds simple? As Nigel would say: "There is a butt", hmmm,
obviously he meant: "There is a BUT!" ;)

  When tiles fall towards the bottom of the game board, you get
penalized for each tile that falls, because a gauge, located at
the right of the game board, will rise according to the number of
"lost" tiles. If that gauge fills up completely, the game is
over...

  If you move tiles and no aligments are made, one tile will
appear somewhere in the lower part of a suspended set of tiles...
just do not let the board fill up completely, because if it
happens, the game will be over.

  Try to make as many alignments of tiles of the same type in one
move, as you get more points...

  Have fun!

